			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				OK guys, 23 pages of &quot;Does anyone know any better than me?&quot;  This is my opinion: Verant is having a great time watching you try to figure out how to do a quest that doesn't work.  He knows it doesn't work that's why the robe isn't quest only.  He said &quot;Well, the quest doesn't work so let's drape it over the guys back as if to say come and take it, and let em kill him for it when they are high enough level.&quot;  I love quests as much as the next guy/gal.  The exp and faction you gain are far more important than the loot, but if I can save myself alot of time and worrying and all I'm really interested in is the loot, I'm going to kill the guy for what I want.  Sorry about the long spawn to you questers.  So for those of you who want to get an Oracle Robe and don't have time to worry about broken quests here are the steps to follow:<BR>
<BR>
1) Lull guard....Caster of lull needs to be like level 40 or so, otherwise you just make him real mad.<BR>
2) Cast snare and Fear on Oracle.  You really should use both<BR>
3) Blast him into the next millinium.<BR>
4) Grab the robe and gate out.<BR>
<BR>
If I have hurt anyones feelings by posting the plan, I'm sorry, but 23 pages worth of angst tells me alot of people are wasting time when they could be enjoying other aspects of the game.  Take care all.
				</font>
